    <stitle>REYCO 101A, 102, 102W SUSPENSIONS - MAINTENANCE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec id="hl0300501">
        <title>MAINTENANCE</title>
        <svcsubsecinfo>
            <para>Reyco suspensions require no lubrication.</para>
            <para>Perform the following inspections periodically: inspect the leaf springs - 101A per the information in
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0300505">Figure 5</hotlnk>, and 102 and 102W per the information in
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0300506">Figure 6</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f0300505" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0300505" filename="../figg03/g0300505.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 5.</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. EQUALIZER MOUNTING BRACKET</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. EQUALIZER BRACKET</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. SPRING ENDS MUST NOT BE IN CONTACT WITH THE SIDES OF THE EQUALIZER BRACKET OR THE
                        SPRING BRACKETS
                    </callout1>
                    <callout1>4. FRONT LEAF SPRING</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f0300506" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0300506" filename="../figg03/g0300506.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 6.</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. EQUALIZER MOUNTING BRACKET</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. EQUALIZER BRACKET</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. SPRING SIDES MUST NOT BE IN CONSTANT CONTACT WITH THE SIDES OF THE EQUALIZER BRACKET OR
                        THE SPRING BRACKETS
                    </callout1>
                    <callout1>4. FRONT LEAF SPRING</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <para>Also, inspect the suspension bolts to ensure correct torque values as specified in the
                <hotlnk document="s03005s_12.xml" xrefid="hl0300502">TORQUE CHART</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <para>Check the vehicle alignment for any of the following reasons:</para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Any fasteners with torque values below the values found in the
                        <hotlnk document="s03005s_12.xml" xrefid="hl0300502">TORQUE CHART</hotlnk>
                        are loose fasteners.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>Finding elongated (stretched) holes on any suspension components.</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Finding excessive or abnormal tire wear.</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>When bushings are replaced.</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Finding any loose fasteners in the suspension system.</para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
        </svcsubsecinfo>
    </svcsubsec>
